{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fairy}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fairy|prevnum=683|prev=Aromatisse|nextnum=685|next=Slurpuff}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Swirlix\n|jname=ペロッパフ\n|tmname=Peroppafu\n|category=Cotton Candy\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fairy\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Sweet Veil\n|abilityd=Unburden\n|ndex=684\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=131\n|height-ftin=1\'04"\n|height-m=0.4\n|weight-lbs=7.7\n|weight-kg=3.5\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Fairy\n|gendercode=127\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evde=1\n|expyield=68\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|color=White\n|catchrate=200\n|body=07\n|pokefordex=swirlix\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Swirlix\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ペロッパフ\'\'\' \'\'Peroppafu\'\') is a {{type|Fairy}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Slurpuff}} when [[trade]]d holding a [[Whipped Dream]].\n\n==Biology==\n[[File:XY Prerelease Swirlix feet.png|thumb|left|150px|Swirlix with both of its feet visible]]\nSwirlix is a small, round Pokémon covered with fluffy white fur. It has reddish pink eyes with white pupils, round ears with light pink tips, a tiny reddish pink nose, and is often seen with its tongue poking out of the corner of its mouth. In between its ears is a more prominent tuft of fur. Poking out of the bottom of its fur is its light pink tail. Its feet are usually tucked up in its fur, but when they are visible, they are seen to be a light pink and have three toes. Swirlix only eats sweets, which makes its fur as sticky as cotton candy. It can entangle its opponents with white sticky thread.\n{{left clear}}\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Swirlix anime.png|thumb|left|250px|Swirlix in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nFive Swirlix appeared in \'\'[[XY026|A Battle by Any Other Name!]]\'\'. They attacked {{an|Serena}} and {{TP|Serena|Fennekin}} after believing they were the ones who stole all of the {{Berries}} in their forest. The misunderstanding was eventually resolved when {{TRT}} was revealed to be the true culprits.\n\nA Swirlix appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Raleigh]]. It was revealed to have evolved into a Slurpuff prior to the events of the {{pkmn|movie}}.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nSwirlix debuted in \'\'[[XY001|Kalos, Where Dreams and Adventures Begin!]]\'\'.\n\nA Swirlix made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[XY021|A PokéVision of Things to Come!]]\'\'.\n\nA Swirlix made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[XY028|The Bonds of Evolution!]]\'\'.\n\nA Swirlix made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[XY031|The Cave of Trials!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Swirlix appeared in \'\'[[XY039|Summer of Discovery!]]\'\', with one under the ownership of a {{pkmn|Trainer}} and the other under the ownership of {{an|Shauna}}. The former was one of the Pokémon that participated in the [[Pokémon Summer Camp]], while the latter was only seen on a [[Pokévision]] video icon. The first Swirlix reappeared in \'\'[[XY041|Foggy Pokémon Orienteering!]]\'\' and \'\'[[XY042|Battling Into the Hall of Fame!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Performer}}\'s Swirlix appeared in \'\'[[XY060|A Showcase Debut!]]\'\', where it participated in the {{ci|Coumarine}} {{pkmn|Showcase}}. It appeared again in \'\'[[XY109|Master Class Choices!]]\'\', where it was used in the {{ci|Fleurrh}} Showcase.\n\nA Swirlix made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[XY062|The Future Is Now, Thanks to Determination!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Swirlix appeared in \'\'[[XY066|Confronting the Darkness!]]\'\'.\n\nA Swirlix appeared in \'\'[[XY078|Lights! Camera! Pika!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Frank]]. Frank used Swirlix alongside {{p|Heliolisk}} and {{p|Magnemite}} to provide the lighting whilst filming his movies.\n\nA Trainer\'s Swirlix appeared in \'\'[[XY080|Performing with Fiery Charm!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Swirlix appeared in \'\'[[XY091|A Performance Pop Quiz!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Swirlix appeared in \'\'[[XY113|Performing a Pathway to the Future!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Swirlix appeared in \'\'[[XY138|The First Day of the Rest of Your Life!]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY026|Swirlix|Ash\'s Pokédex|Swirlix, the Cotton Candy Pokémon. Swirlix only eats sweets making its fur as sticky as cotton candy.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Swirlix Adventures.png|thumb|250px|Swirlix in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n\nA Swirlix ran away with its Trainer when {{p|Xerneas}} and {{p|Yveltal}} clashed in Vaniville Town in \'\'[[PAXY02|X-actly What They Wanted]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Swirlix (TCG)}}\n\n==Other appearances==\n===[[Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS/Wii U]]===\n[[File:Swirlix SSB4.png|thumb|240px|Swirlix in [[Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS/Wii U|Super Smash Bros. for 3DS.]]]]\nSwirlix appears as a {{i|Poké Ball}} summon in both versions of the game. It uses {{m|Cotton Spore}} to slow down nearby opponents.\n\n====Trophy information====\n\'\'\'NA\'\'\': \'\'Swirlix, a Fairy-type Pokémon, has a serious sweet tooth. However, all those sweets make its fur really sticky. If you trade a Swirlix while it holds Whipped Dream, it\'ll evolve into a Slurpuff. In Smash Bros., Swirlix likes to use Cotton Spore. Getting hit by this attack will seriously slow you down.\'\'\n\n\'\'\'PAL\'\'\': \'\'Swirlix has a serious sweet tooth - it eats so many sweets that even its fur is sticky and sweet. Not that you should try eating its fur. In this game, it\'ll use Cotton Spore to slow down all of the other fighters. See? Definitely not edible. Fun fact: if you trade Swirlix while it\'s holding a Whipped Dream, it\'ll evolve!\'\'\n\n===[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]===\nSwirlix returns as a Pokémon summoned from the Poké Ball, retaining the same behavior from the previous game.\n{{-}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n*{{g|Super Mystery Dungeon}}: Swirlix is the stewardess for the [[Expedition Society]]. She is also a glutton, so she eats much of the food she makes.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=fairy}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=131|label1=Central|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|t=FFF|v=Alpha Sapphire|entry=Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n[[Category:Pokémon in the Galar Pokédex]]<!--\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=VIII|reg1=Galar|num1=???}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Sword|v2=Shield|entry=TBD}}\n|}\n|}-->\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=fairy}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Entry1|2|v=X|t=FFF|area={{rt|7|kalos}}, [[Friend Safari]] ([[Friend Safari#Fairy-type Safari|Fairy]])}}\n{{Availability/Entry1|2|v=Y|area=[[Friend Safari]] ([[Friend Safari#Fairy-type Safari|Fairy]])}}\n{{Availability/Entry2/None||v=Omega Ruby|v2=Alpha Sapphire}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VII}}\n{{Availability/Entry2/None|v=Sun|v2=Moon|area=[[Pokémon Bank]]}}\n{{Availability/Entry2/None|v=Ultra Sun|v2=Ultra Moon|area=[[Pokémon Bank]]}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Availability/Footer}}\n\n====In side games====\n{{Availability/Header|type=Fairy}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Entry1|1|v=Battle Trozei|color={{defense color}}|area=[[Blade-and-Shield Path#Stage 6|Blade-and-Shield Path: Stage 6]]}}\n{{Availability/Entry1|1|v=Shuffle|color={{beauty color}}|area=[[Night Festival|Night Fest